author: COMSOL
description: A 3D diesel particulate filter is modeled using coupled mass, heat, and momentum transfer interfaces. The walls are porous, allowing gas to pass through them while at the same time separating particles from the flow. The averaged concentration, temperature, and flow fields are studied. A dynamic representation of soot build-up in the filter takes into account particle deposition as well as catalytic carbon oxidation.
